    <title>Preface</title>
    <para>Test Test2 Test3 Test4</para>
    <para>This guide assists <phrase os="openstack">OpenStack</phrase><phrase os="rack">Rackspace</phrase> writers and
        developers to use an XML-based tool set to create content and
        generate documentation artifacts. </para>
    <para>The components of this tool chain are:<itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Content
                        management</emphasis>. XML and WADL source
                    files are stored in git and SVN.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Authoring</emphasis>.
                    Writers create and edit XML and WADL source files
                    in a <link
                        xlink:href="http://docs.rackspace.com/oxygen"
                        >customized version</link> of the <link
                        xlink:href="http://www.oxygenxml.com/">oXygen
                        XML Editor</link> that includes the Maven
                        <literal>clouddocs</literal> plugin. </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Production</emphasis>.
                    Writers generate documentation artifacts from
                    DocBook XML and WADL source files. The tools and
                    build logic to generate documentation artifacts
                    are implemented as a Maven plugin. </para>
                <para>Apache Maven is a build automation tool. </para>
                <para>Maven reads the configuration for a project from
                    a <literal>pom.xml</literal> file, downloads any
                    required dependencies such as the tools required
                    to build, and produces the specified artifacts. </para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist></para>
</preface>
